[SN]TITLE[SN]
Google unveils 'chatty' Pixel smartphones

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Google has placed a virtual assistant at the heart of two new smartphones it has designed in-house.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
4 October 2016 Last updated at 17:42 BST
The two Pixel handsets are the first mobiles to trigger Google Assistant by holding down their home buttons, somewhat like Apple's Siri.
The BBC's Rory Cellan-Jones asked the Pixel project manager James Nugent why people would want to talk to their devices.
